flict which occurred in 952 between the sons of Hywel Dda and the princes lievav and lago. Gwedwr would translate ' a speaker.'"],"variants":[]},{"name":"Hir","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Sier  , unexplained. This surname is very rare in Germany.","Czech (<b>Šír</b>): nickname from Middle High German <i>schīr</i> ‘sheer, pure, clean’. Compare   Schier  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Sier","meanings":["Dutch and German: from a short form of the personal name <i>Sierik</i>, <i>Sierich</i>, composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>sigi</i> ‘victory’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power(ful)’, or from a short form of the personal name <i>Sigihard</i>, composed of the ancient Germanic elements <i>sigi</i> + <i>hari</i> ‘army’.","English: variant of   Syer  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gwaithfoed ap Gwrdyr Hir was born in 0955, in Flintshire, Wales, his father, Gwrydr ap Caradog, was 35 and his mother, MORFYDD VERCH OWAIN, was 36. He had at least 4 sons. He died on 8 May 1038, in Llanfair Caereinion, Montgomeryshire, Wales, at the age of 83."},"et":{"0955–8 May 1038":"0955–8. mai 1038","0955–1038":"0955–1038","0975–1025":"0975–1025","0990–1027":"0990–1027","0999–Male":"0999–Surnud","0920–0962":"0920–0962","0920–Female":"0920–Surnud","0920":"0920","0975":"0975","0962":"0962","1027":"1027","1038":"1038","1025":"1025","0990":"0990","8 May 1038":"8. mai 1038","0955":"0955","0999":"0999","Llanfair Caereinion, Montgomeryshire, Wales":"Llanfair Caereinion, Montgomeryshire, Wales","Tegeingl, Flintshire, Wales":"Flintshire, Wales"},"fi":{"0955–8 May 1038":"0955–8. toukokuuta 1038","0955–1038":"0955–1038","0975–1025":"0975–1025","0990–1027":"0990–1027","0999–Male":"0999–Kuollut","0920–0962":"0920–0962","0920–Female":"0920–Kuollut","0920":"0920","0975":"0975","0962":"0962","1027":"1027","1038":"1038","1025":"1025","0990":"0990","8 May 1038":"8. toukokuuta 1038","0955":"0955","0999":"0999","Llanfair Caerei